metadata.name: The Rifting #52
metadata.description:
Generative artwork inspired by the effects of plate tectonics.
*click and wait for the music to fade in

There are four different rifts with 'Basin & Range' being the rarest.

The song is called 'The Rifting' originally released in 2018 by my alter ego 'Polynia'.
It was made by sampling some tape loops with an Akai S1000,
then playing the samples with a midikeyboard, finally recording an improv with a Tascam 4-track tape recorder.

You can find it here:
https://polynia.bandcamp.com/track/the-rifting
or on all streaming platforms.

Created with Hydra

Genesis artwork by pxlshrd
Twitter: @pxlshrd

metadata.name: Line haven #230
metadata.description:
Primarily, I use lines to create images or designs. It is characterized by simplicity and minimalism, and I focused on using clean and precise lines to convey shapes, forms, and textures. Also emphasized outlines, color palettes, and subject lines rather than shadows to create a more substantial visual impact.
I expressed this idea through lines with simplicity and clarity to leave room for interpretation by the viewer. One of the advantages of line art is its versatility. I combined lines with geometric shapes to add depth and texture to the image. 
Overall, I tried to offer a unique way of expressing creativity by focusing on clean lines and minimal aesthetics, and I believe that lines can have an eternal charm that will continue to captivate audiences in various artistic media such as digital art.

Made by p5.js
s = save

metadata.name: Einstein-Rosen Memories #44
metadata.description:
At first this was 'just' an attempt at visualizing my childhood imagination of wormholes.
As I worked on the code and the more the fusion of music and visuals took me over, the more this piece led me to deeper thoughts.
How vague can something be in order to really exist?

Well, this, of course raised many new questions.
Questions about space-time, about metaphysical assumptions, about the transmission of thoughts and feelings and so on.

The longer you ask yourself about these things, the more the boundary between fiction and reality becomes blurred, because there really is none.

///
Click for audio.
png screenshot: 's' in live view (I highly recommend doing this!).

No rarity features this time, your taste decides.
The music was written and recorded on December 15th, 2020 on a Tascam 4-track tape recorder. 

PLEASE NOTE:
The thumbnails do not reflect the actual artwork.
(See them as another layer of vague memories)
